## âš™ï¸ **2. Computer Architecture Overview**

### ğŸ§© **2.1 The Three Foundational Components**

```mermaid
graph TD
    CPU((ğŸ§  CPU)) 
    Memory((ğŸ’¾ Memory))
    Storage((ğŸ“¦ Storage))

    CPU --> Memory
    Memory --> Storage
    Storage --> CPU
```

#### **CPU (Central Processing Unit)**

* Executes instructions
* Handles arithmetic & logic operations
* Controls the entire system

#### **Memory (RAM)**

* Temporary workspace
* Extremely fast
* Volatile (data erased when powered off)

#### **Storage (SSD/HDD)**

* Permanent data storage
* Slower than RAM
* Holds OS, apps, files

